WEBVTT

02:34.767 --> 02:36.667
- Mercy
is the compassion we feel

02:36.734 --> 02:38.800
for someone else's misfortune.

02:38.867 --> 02:42.767
Mercy compels us
to alleviate that misfortune.

02:42.834 --> 02:45.767
Mercy is a child of charity,
but the sister of justice

02:45.834 --> 02:48.000
because both are about
the invisible link

02:48.066 --> 02:50.467
that exists between people.

02:50.533 --> 02:56.166
Mercy is spontaneous
because misery is involuntary.

02:56.233 --> 02:58.600
- At approximately 3:15 p.m.,

02:58.667 --> 03:00.467
as your children were
walking home from school

03:00.533 --> 03:04.300
with four classmates, a blue
van pulled up beside them.

03:04.367 --> 03:06.066
A male Caucasian stepped out.

03:06.133 --> 03:08.700
The man approached Gary
and Holly saying that you,

03:08.767 --> 03:11.333
Mrs. Beecher, had asked him
to pick them up.

03:11.400 --> 03:14.100
Gary was reluctant at first,
but eventually

03:14.166 --> 03:17.233
the man persuaded him,
using Pokemon cards.

03:17.300 --> 03:20.600
The van then drove off
to the east side of town.

03:20.667 --> 03:23.734
- So what's being done
to find them?

03:23.800 --> 03:26.233
- Kidnapping
is a waiting game, Sister.

03:26.300 --> 03:28.233
We have to wait
to be contacted.

03:28.300 --> 03:29.367
- And what if you're not?

03:29.433 --> 03:31.400
- Milk cartons.
- Toby.

03:31.467 --> 03:33.300
- Come on,
Schillinger did this.

03:33.367 --> 03:35.367
- We have no proof of that.
- Oh, for fuck's sake.

03:35.433 --> 03:36.500
Who else?!

03:36.567 --> 03:38.533
- You come from
a wealthy family.

03:38.600 --> 03:40.867
Most likely we have
a ransom situation.

03:40.934 --> 03:44.166
- You are fucking this up,
you asshole!

03:46.433 --> 03:48.367
Find my goddamn kids!

03:48.433 --> 03:49.633
- Oh, my God!

03:49.700 --> 03:51.533
- Find my goddamn kids!

03:51.600 --> 03:53.600
- Get them out! Out!

03:56.834 --> 03:59.333
- Find my kids!

04:02.367 --> 04:04.266
Ughhh!

04:04.333 --> 04:07.600
- I don't know anything
about a kidnapping.

04:07.667 --> 04:09.967
- Beecher seems to
think you do.

04:10.033 --> 04:11.533
That you're behind this.

04:11.600 --> 04:14.667
- He and I have had a lot of
shit happen between us, so...

04:14.734 --> 04:17.400
I can understand him
saying that.

04:17.467 --> 04:21.100
But Beecher and I have
one thing in common, too.

04:21.166 --> 04:22.700
We're both fathers.

04:22.767 --> 04:24.967
I lost a son.

04:25.033 --> 04:28.467
I know what
he's going through.

04:30.700 --> 04:32.867
- I'm sorry about what
happened in the library.

04:32.967 --> 04:35.200
I just got so frustrated.

04:35.233 --> 04:36.367
- I know, I know.

04:36.433 --> 04:38.166
You might want to
call your mother.

04:38.233 --> 04:39.533
She's pretty upset.

04:39.600 --> 04:40.700
We talked about it
in the car.

04:40.767 --> 04:44.467
Toby, the reasons
you're in here, the...

04:44.533 --> 04:46.300
the alcoholism

04:46.367 --> 04:50.166
and hitting the little
Brockwell girl...

04:50.233 --> 04:52.867
your mother and I
can't help but think

04:52.934 --> 04:56.166
that we're...to blame
for so much of it.

04:56.233 --> 04:57.500
- Dad--
- No.

04:57.567 --> 04:59.333
We failed you growing up.

04:59.400 --> 05:01.667
- Look, as much as
I'd like to blame you

05:01.734 --> 05:04.700
for the miserable shithole
my life has become,

05:04.767 --> 05:08.233
what's wrong with me
is inside me.

05:08.300 --> 05:10.333
I own it.

05:10.400 --> 05:14.133
And either I have to control it
or it will control me.

05:15.934 --> 05:17.934
Right now, I just want
to hold my babies.

05:20.967 --> 05:27.000
- So...our sweet young things
are safe and sound?

05:27.066 --> 05:28.433
- Yeah.

05:28.500 --> 05:29.734
- All right.

05:29.800 --> 05:34.200
Time to kick this thing
into overdrive.

05:34.266 --> 05:37.000
I want you to send the package.

05:37.066 --> 05:39.133
- Dad, you sure?

05:39.200 --> 05:40.567
- Yes.

05:40.633 --> 05:43.066
- 'Cause I been thinking.

05:43.133 --> 05:46.200
Like you know I've never had
a problem with breaking the law.

05:46.266 --> 05:50.033
I'm talking about at most
a couple stolen Camrys.

05:50.100 --> 05:51.200
This kidnapping...

05:51.266 --> 05:53.600
- Keep your voice down.

05:54.834 --> 05:57.333
- This kind of thing's
really not my style.

05:57.400 --> 05:59.266
- I'll pay you double.

06:01.967 --> 06:03.367
- Okay.

06:06.967 --> 06:09.700
- Are you Les Hibitz?

06:09.767 --> 06:11.967
- Yeah.
- Tobias Beecher.

06:12.033 --> 06:14.300
Mind if I join you?

06:14.367 --> 06:16.800
- You want to sit with me?
- Yeah.

06:16.867 --> 06:19.867
- Ha ha. Nobody ever
wants to sit with me.

06:23.433 --> 06:26.633
- I understand you did some Fed
time for kidnapping, right?

06:26.700 --> 06:29.066
- Yeah, I was framed.

06:29.133 --> 06:30.567
- Yeah, I'm sure you were.

06:30.633 --> 06:33.400
But I, um, don't know
if you've heard,

06:33.467 --> 06:35.166
but my two children
were abducted recently.

06:35.233 --> 06:37.133
- I had nothing to do with it.

06:37.200 --> 06:39.033
- I know, what I'm asking is--

06:39.100 --> 06:42.100
I was wondering if you might
be able to look into it.

06:42.166 --> 06:44.367
Find out if somebody
was hired to do the job.

06:44.433 --> 06:47.066
- I could ask around,
see what I could find out,

06:47.133 --> 06:50.633
but...I wouldn't
hold out much hope.

06:52.300 --> 06:55.800
So do you like Def Leppard?

06:56.800 --> 06:58.967
- Years and years and years ago,

06:59.033 --> 07:00.533
the Catholic church made a list

07:00.600 --> 07:02.567
of all the ways
we can show mercy.

07:02.633 --> 07:04.867
Feed the hungry,
give drink to the thirsty,

07:04.934 --> 07:07.066
clothe the naked,
shit like that.

07:07.133 --> 07:09.700
Another of them
was ransom the captive.

07:09.767 --> 07:12.333
In those days,
pirates and infidels and such

07:12.400 --> 07:15.533
would abduct fair maidens
and Christian pilgrims.

07:15.600 --> 07:19.900
God-fearing people were expected
to pay for their return.

07:19.967 --> 07:22.800
Who gets to ransom the captive
in this day and age?

07:22.867 --> 07:26.467
Instead, we're expected
to visit the imprisoned.

07:26.533 --> 07:28.533
That's right.

07:28.600 --> 07:30.667
Come on down!

07:41.367 --> 07:43.233
Break it up, you two.

07:52.467 --> 07:55.066
- You okay?
- Oh, shit, yeah.

07:55.133 --> 07:57.667
Hey, man, they stab me,
they shoot me--

07:57.734 --> 08:01.100
I ain't going down.

08:01.166 --> 08:02.233
How you doing?

08:07.500 --> 08:09.066
- My kids.

08:09.133 --> 08:10.266
- I heard.
That's fucked up.

08:10.333 --> 08:12.100
I'm sorry, man.

08:13.567 --> 08:16.100
- I feel so goddamn helpless.

08:17.333 --> 08:19.033
- I bet.

08:19.100 --> 08:22.900
- At least the baby...
Harry's safe.

08:22.967 --> 08:24.734
- Toby, they're gonna
be all right, you hear me?

08:24.800 --> 08:26.433
They're gonna be okay.

08:26.500 --> 08:28.266
They're gonna be fine.

08:31.066 --> 08:33.266
Ah...

08:36.667 --> 08:38.633
- Oh, man.

08:39.800 --> 08:42.100
- I missed you.

08:42.166 --> 08:44.233
- Me, too.

09:02.867 --> 09:05.233
- Keller's back
in Emerald City.

09:05.300 --> 09:08.266
Two lovebirds
have reunited.

09:08.333 --> 09:10.734
- And I hope they enjoy
their evening together.

09:10.800 --> 09:13.900
It's gonna be
the last night of sleep...

09:13.967 --> 09:19.100
or peace that Beecher's gonna
have for a long, long time.

09:42.500 --> 09:44.000
- Chris?

09:44.066 --> 09:46.667
- Sorry, did I wake you?

09:52.100 --> 09:53.700
- Hey.

09:53.767 --> 09:56.600
What's the matter?

09:56.667 --> 09:59.300
- Toby, I died.

10:00.600 --> 10:03.633
And there's no white light.

10:05.200 --> 10:06.800
I was there,
but they brought me back.

10:06.867 --> 10:07.900
But I was there, Toby.

10:07.967 --> 10:09.400
I was in hell,
and I felt everything.

10:09.467 --> 10:12.000
I felt the pain and I felt
the fire for all eternity.

10:12.066 --> 10:14.266
- Hey, hey.
It's gonna be okay.

10:14.333 --> 10:16.433
- No, it's not gonna be okay.
Don't fucking lie to me.

10:16.500 --> 10:18.734
I was there, Toby.
They're bringing me back.

10:18.800 --> 10:20.533
- You know what's funny?

10:23.166 --> 10:25.700
You got pissed at me for
talking to Said about God,

10:25.767 --> 10:28.300
but that's what I was
talking to him about.

10:28.367 --> 10:34.967
'Cause if all that's left
for us in this life is Oz,

10:35.033 --> 10:39.667
then we better start
thinking about what's next,

10:39.734 --> 10:41.667
what comes after.

10:48.000 --> 10:49.667
- Don't let go.

10:52.000 --> 10:54.133
- Okay, okay.

11:06.300 --> 11:07.734
- Tobias.

11:07.800 --> 11:11.033
I didn't expect to see you here
today given what's going on.

11:11.100 --> 11:13.900
- Yeah, well,
work helps keep my mind

11:13.967 --> 11:15.667
from caving in on itself.

11:15.734 --> 11:17.166
- Oh, I hear that.

11:17.233 --> 11:19.367
It's a madhouse outside,

11:19.433 --> 11:21.100
though the crowd of
protesters is smaller.

11:21.166 --> 11:23.934
I'm afraid people are getting
used to capital punishment.

11:24.000 --> 11:27.000
- Sister Pete,
I need to ask you a favor.

11:27.066 --> 11:29.066
- If I can,
you know I will.

11:29.133 --> 11:30.900
What?

11:30.967 --> 11:33.900
- Talk to Chris.

11:33.967 --> 11:35.734
- Now, how is it
that you ask me

11:35.800 --> 11:37.767
the one thing
that I won't do?

11:37.834 --> 11:39.934
- He feels terrible.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.934
- Tobias, he tried to
use me to get to you.

11:44.000 --> 11:45.967
Now he's using you
to get to me.

11:46.033 --> 11:48.567
I will not  play his game.

11:48.633 --> 11:50.900
- He's afraid that
if you leave the convent,

11:50.967 --> 11:52.233
he's gonna burn forever.

11:52.300 --> 11:54.867
- Oh, he's gonna burn all right,
but not for that.

11:54.934 --> 11:57.767
He's gonna burn for all of
the other people he's hurt,

11:57.834 --> 11:59.533
all of the other lives
he's destroyed,

11:59.600 --> 12:01.333
including yours.

12:09.934 --> 12:11.400
- We've been going
through the records

12:11.467 --> 12:13.467
of various prisoners
at Emerald City.

12:13.533 --> 12:16.166
One pops out as a potential
connection to the kidnapping.

12:16.233 --> 12:17.367
- Who?

12:17.433 --> 12:18.734
- Christopher Keller.

12:18.800 --> 12:20.433
- No.

12:20.500 --> 12:21.567
Chris is my friend.

12:21.633 --> 12:23.900
- Let me see that.

12:23.967 --> 12:26.700
- Keller broke every
bone in your body.

12:26.767 --> 12:28.100
- He's the one?

12:28.166 --> 12:29.600
- He also saved my life
from Schillinger.

12:29.667 --> 12:32.333
I'm telling you,
Schillinger is responsible.

12:32.400 --> 12:35.200
- "Armed robbery,
assault, kidnapping."

12:35.266 --> 12:37.100
- He wasn't convicted.

12:37.166 --> 12:39.433
- "Police suspect him of raping,
torturing and murdering

12:39.500 --> 12:41.133
several homosexual men"?

12:41.200 --> 12:44.266
- It can't be him.
It's not him.

12:44.333 --> 12:47.400
- How can you be so sure?

12:48.367 --> 12:50.000
- I know Chris, Mother...

12:51.300 --> 12:53.066
Intimately.

12:53.133 --> 12:54.967
- Intimately?

12:57.967 --> 12:59.667
- He's my lover.

13:16.767 --> 13:19.033
- Holy shit.

13:19.100 --> 13:21.467
Vern, you better
come see this.

13:21.533 --> 13:22.600
- What do you got?

13:22.667 --> 13:24.934
- Package
for Tobias Beecher.

13:25.000 --> 13:26.100
Look.

13:26.166 --> 13:28.066
- Jesus Christ.

13:28.133 --> 13:32.033
Officer Howell?
We got a problem here.

13:35.266 --> 13:36.800
- What the hell is that?

13:36.867 --> 13:39.166
- A child's hand.

14:23.934 --> 14:26.066
- Leave us alone.

14:29.633 --> 14:31.834
How you holding up?

14:34.100 --> 14:36.133
- A few days in the Hole

14:36.200 --> 14:38.600
only increases
my credibility with Pancamo,

14:38.667 --> 14:40.900
Adebisi, and Morales.

14:40.967 --> 14:42.700
Ever spent any
time in here?

14:42.767 --> 14:44.800
- No.

14:44.867 --> 14:46.533
- Good.

14:52.667 --> 14:55.400
You look like shit.

14:55.467 --> 14:57.900
- So I'm in?
- "So I'm in."

14:57.967 --> 15:00.400
Adebisi
ain't convinced, man.

15:00.467 --> 15:02.533
Looks like you're gonna
have to take another test.

15:02.600 --> 15:05.266
Oh, yeah.

15:06.467 --> 15:08.767
- We going to box?
- We wanna see

15:08.834 --> 15:10.033
if you can take a punch.

15:10.100 --> 15:12.266
- Or two.

15:12.333 --> 15:14.400
- You got a problem
with me, man?

15:14.467 --> 15:15.934
- Oh ho ho ho!

15:16.000 --> 15:18.300
- Yeah, you're weak.

15:18.367 --> 15:20.700
- Give me gloves.

15:20.767 --> 15:23.767
- Well, actually,
we're not gonna spar.

15:23.834 --> 15:25.934
- No?
- No.

15:26.000 --> 15:29.233
I'm gonna use you
for a heavy bag.

15:29.300 --> 15:32.467
- And the rest of us bet on
how long you stay standing.

15:34.166 --> 15:35.100
- Ready?

15:37.333 --> 15:38.266
- Yeah.

15:38.333 --> 15:40.433
- Ding, ding.

15:40.500 --> 15:42.266
inmates: Oh!

15:48.133 --> 15:49.333
- He's gettin' up.

15:51.734 --> 15:52.700
- Oh!

15:57.367 --> 15:59.233
- 15 seconds.

15:59.300 --> 16:01.100
I win.
Pay up.

16:11.734 --> 16:13.467
- Ow!

16:13.533 --> 16:15.767
Yo, real impressive.

16:15.834 --> 16:17.533
- Yeah, thanks.

16:17.600 --> 16:21.066
Your bruises must hurt.

16:21.133 --> 16:23.433
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

16:23.500 --> 16:26.633
Brought you a little something
to sooth your wounds.

16:30.033 --> 16:32.033
Later.

16:59.867 --> 17:01.333
- Yo.

17:03.333 --> 17:05.100
What the fuck
is you doing?

17:05.934 --> 17:08.900
- Breakfast of champions.

17:30.734 --> 17:32.000
You wanted to see me?

17:32.066 --> 17:34.300
- We just took a straw
poll on you.

17:34.367 --> 17:36.467
- I voted yes.

17:36.533 --> 17:38.567
- I voted no.
- I abstained.

17:38.633 --> 17:40.333
- A tie.

17:40.400 --> 17:42.667
- How do I break this tie?

17:43.967 --> 17:45.700
- There's a final test.

17:45.767 --> 17:47.567
- Which is?

17:49.834 --> 17:51.700
- You gotta kill somebody.

17:51.767 --> 17:53.200
- Who?

17:53.266 --> 17:54.567
- Anybody.

17:54.633 --> 17:56.200
We don't care.

17:59.533 --> 18:02.934
- All right.
I'll do it.

18:29.266 --> 18:31.166
- Pete.

18:31.233 --> 18:32.834
I have terrible news.

18:32.900 --> 18:34.000
- Oh, my God, what?

18:34.066 --> 18:37.433
- The Cardinal is coming.

18:37.500 --> 18:39.633
- Cardinal Abgott
is coming to Oz?

18:39.700 --> 18:41.300
- He wants to say a mass,

18:41.367 --> 18:43.266
meet with the staff,
and then with some prisoners.

18:43.333 --> 18:46.300
- You're friends
with him, right?

18:46.367 --> 18:48.200
- I worked with him
in his office

18:48.266 --> 18:49.734
until
he transferred me here.

18:49.800 --> 18:53.867
I...disagreed with him
once too often.

18:55.800 --> 18:58.200
- I'm taking the day off.

18:58.266 --> 19:00.166
Oh, no, you can't!

19:00.233 --> 19:03.100
- Ray, I have one foot
out of the convent door.

19:03.166 --> 19:05.100
I think hobnobbing
with the Cardinal

19:05.166 --> 19:07.233
would be just a little
hypocritical, don't you?

19:07.300 --> 19:10.467
- Yeah, well, he specifically
asked to meet you.

19:10.533 --> 19:12.300
- Me?
Why?

19:12.367 --> 19:14.700
- Well, apparently
this whole thing started

19:14.767 --> 19:17.967
because his Eminence received
a letter from a prisoner.

19:19.767 --> 19:20.934
- Which one?

19:21.000 --> 19:23.467
- Chris Keller.

19:23.533 --> 19:26.233
- Chris Keller.
Of course.

19:31.066 --> 19:32.734
- Raymond.

19:32.800 --> 19:35.934
- Cardinal Abgott,
it's good of you to come.

19:36.000 --> 19:39.066
- It's a pleasure
to see you, son.

19:39.133 --> 19:40.667
Let's suit up.

19:47.667 --> 19:51.200
Do you know why
I transferred you to Oswald?

19:53.433 --> 19:55.500
- I had too many opinions?

19:57.100 --> 19:59.000
- You had too big an ego.

20:00.533 --> 20:01.633
- Probably.

20:01.700 --> 20:04.166
- Something tells me
that's changed.

